2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of cooperative communication in wireless networks, which is a key topic in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a strategy for cooperative communication that can be applied to different channel models, which is related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may have implications for multimedia applications in wireless networks, as cooperative communication can improve the quality of service for multimedia traffic. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may have security implications for cooperative communication, as it proposes a strategy that can be universally optimal for different channel models.
